How to install python on macOS

1. Check if Python is already installed 
Go to the terminal and write python3 --version
If it matches the most recent downloadable version from : https://www.python.org/downloads/, 
go straight to starting coding

2. If it does not match the recent downloadable version from : https://www.python.org/downloads/,
click on download Python symbol on the website.

Double click on the .pkg file that is titled "Install Python" and follow the instructions

Check where this version of python is saved and copy paste it to the applications

3. now write python3 --version and check again in the terminal 
4. Write a code file in python saved with the extension ".py"

5. Run on terminal by writing python3 filename.py
